1 Download Ubuntu 6.06 Server https://old-releases.ubuntu.com/releases/6.06.0/ Find Server install CD Then Select What Architecture SPARC Or HP PA-RISC Or IA-64
2 Flash The Iso
3 When on installer menu install to the hard disk
4 Setup Ubuntu Server 6.06 Until Finished
5 After Finish The Installation Run sudo nano /boot/grub/menu.lst Then go to End Default Options
  Then change title Ubuntu, kernel 2.6.15-51-server to Linux Mint, kernel 2.6.15-51
  Then change Recovery mode title Ubuntu, kernel 2.6.15-51-server (recovery mode)to Linux Mint, kernel 2.6.15-51 (recovery mode)
  Then change Ubuntu, memtest86+ To Linux Mint, memtest86+
  Ctrl x y enter no need update-grub it uses grub legacy
6 Run sudo nano /etc/issue then change Ubuntu 6.06.2 LTS \n \l To Linux Mint 1.0 Ada \n \l then ctrl x y enter
  Then Run sudo nano /etc/issue.net then change Ubuntu 6.06.2 LTS To Linux Mint 1.0 Ada then ctrl x y enter
7 Run sudo rm /etc/motd
8 Edit apt sources using sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list
   Then remove Line commented out by installer and Replace existing lines with old-releases URLs
   Use this template

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper main restricted universe multiverse

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-updates main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-updates main restricted universe multiverse

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-security main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-security main restricted universe multiverse

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-backports main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-backports main restricted universe multiverse

Update package lists
sudo apt-get update

9 If your SPARC Or HP PA-RISC Or IA-64 Hardware Support KDE Run sudo apt-get install kubuntu-desktop since linux mint 1.0 uses kde
  If it doesnt support desktop environment you will ended up in very minimal base system

10 Run sudo reboot and Enjoy your Linux Mint Port For SPARC HP PA-RISC And IA-64
